    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-07-27T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="598"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d598">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/5108: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-07-27T13:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1923—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 27—10:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>264. Following telegram received from commander of Yangtze patrol dated July
                    23rd.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“On July 17th General Chow, commanding Kweichow troops and guarding the right
                        bank of river opposite Chungking, treacherously revolted and went over to
                        the first army, crossed river and took Kiangpei cutting off Chungking from
                        down river. On July 20th S.S. <hi rend="italic">Alice Dollar</hi> was shot
                        at by his troops on her way to Chungking. <pb facs="0862" n="746"
                            xml:id="pg_746"/> On July 21st <hi rend="italic">Alice Dollar</hi> on
                        departure was escorted by <hi rend="italic">Monocacy</hi>, Lieutenant
                        Commander Nielson, both <hi rend="italic">Alice Dollar</hi> and <hi
                            rend="italic">Monocacy</hi> were shot at. <hi rend="italic"
                            >Monocacy</hi> returned the [fire] with her battery. Attack on American
                        flag wholly unjustified and unprovoked. On July 22nd <hi rend="italic"
                            >Palos</hi> reported conditions normal at Chungking; General Chow
                        Hsi-cheng has retreated to Kweichow. It would appear that <hi rend="italic"
                            >Monocacy</hi> action has defeated a forcible attempt to establish an
                        illegal blockade of the river whereby foreign community in Chungking would
                        have been cut off.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
